<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>3DCG: Scaling</title>
    <%= stylesheets('3dcg', 'box2') %>
    <%= scripts('jquery', 'jquery-ui', 'underscore', 'ace/ace', 'source-editor') %>
    <style>
      img.large {
        width: 60%;
      }

      video {
        margin: 10px auto;
      }
    </style>

    <script type="text/x-mathjax-config">
      MathJax.Hub.Config({tex2jax: {inlineMath: [['$','$'], ['\\(','\\)']]}});
    </script>
    <script type="text/javascript" async src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/mathjax/2.7.1/MathJax.js?config=TeX-AMS_CHTML"></script>
  </head>

  <body>
    <header>
      Scaling
    </header>
    <div id="contents">
      <%= overview(reading_material: ['design/transformations', 'math/transformations/3d/scaling'] ) %>
      <section>
        <h1>Preview</h1>
        <%= raytrace_movie 'demo' %>
        <%= source 'demo.chai' %>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h1>Implementation</h1>
        <aside class="boxed2">
          <h1>Task</h1>
          <p>
            Examine the file ``math/transformation-matrices.h``.
            You will find functions that just might be quite helpful to you.
          </p>
        </aside>
        <aside class="boxed2">
          <h1>Task</h1>
          <p>
            Open ``math/transformation3d.cpp``. Use ``math::transformations::translation`` as a guide for this task.
          </p>
          <p>
            Define a function ``math::transformations::scale(double sx, double sy, double sz)`` in ``math/transformation3d.cpp``.
            Expose it to the rest of the application by adding a declaration in the corresponding header.
          </p>
        </aside>
        <p>
          Lastly, we need to define a scaling ``Primitive``. The ``Transformer`` class models the primitive responsible
          for all transformations and has already been written for you. What remains for you to do is to initialize it so that it scales.
        </p>
        <aside class="boxed2">
          <h1>Task</h1>
          <p>
            Define a factory function ``Primitive raytracer::primitives::scale(double sx, double sy, double sz, Primitive transformee)`` in ``primitives/transformer-primitive.cpp``.
            Use the given function ``raytracer::primitives::translate`` as a guide.
          </p>
        </aside>
        <aside class="boxed2">
          <h1>Task</h1>
          <p>
            Add the necessary bindings to the scripting language.
          </p>
        </aside>
        <aside class="boxed2">
          <h1>Task</h1>
          <p>
            Check your implementation extensively.
          </p>
        </aside>
      </section>  
    </div>
  </body>

  <script>
    function initialize()
    {
      SourceEditor.initialize();
    }

    $( initialize );   
  </script>
</html>
